President Biden has announced his intention to nominate former Maryland Governor Martin O'Malley as Commissioner of the Social Security Administration. O'Malley is known for his commitment to making government more accessible and transparent. He has a track record of enhancing government services and improving critical services for millions of people. Congressional leaders, state and local government officials, and community, advocacy, and labor organizations have expressed their support for O'Malley's nomination, citing his experience and leadership qualities. They believe he will be an effective leader in protecting and strengthening Social Security for future generations.